---
import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
import Schema from '../../components/Schema.astro';
import { SITE } from '../../lib/site';

const refrigPrices = [
  { item: 'Diagnostic visit (commercial, business hours)', min: 129, max: 169 },
  { item: 'Walk-in condenser fan motor', min: 480, max: 880 },
  { item: 'Reach-in compressor relay / start kit', min: 220, max: 380 },
  { item: 'Door gasket replacement (per door)', min: 180, max: 320 },
  { item: 'Ice machine cleaning + descaling', min: 280, max: 520 },
  { item: 'Quarterly preventive maintenance contract', min: 320, max: 640 },
];

const faqs = [
  { q: 'How much does commercial refrigeration repair cost?', a: 'Commercial diagnostic is $129–$169. Common 2026 repairs: walk-in condenser fan motor $480–$880; reach-in compressor relay $220–$380; door gasket replacement $180–$320 per door; ice machine cleaning + descaling $280–$520. Quotes are flat-rate before work begins.' },
  { q: 'What commercial refrigeration equipment do you service?', a: 'Walk-in coolers and freezers, reach-in refrigerators, undercounter units, prep tables, ice machines, beverage coolers, and light-commercial display cases. We serve restaurants, cafés, convenience stores, small grocers, florists, and medical/lab facilities across Tampa Bay.' },
  { q: 'Do you handle urgent refrigeration calls?', a: 'Yes. Walk-in failures cost product every minute, so we prioritize operating businesses ahead of routine work when urgent calls come in. We give a realistic ETA before dispatch.' },
  { q: 'Will you sign a preventive maintenance agreement?', a: 'Yes — quarterly or monthly PM contracts ($320–$640 per quarter depending on equipment count) include coil cleaning, defrost cycle verification, door-gasket inspection, drain flushing, temperature calibration, refrigerant leak scan, and a health-inspector-ready written report.' },
  { q: 'Do you work on ice machines?', a: 'Yes. Manitowoc, Hoshizaki, Scotsman, Ice-O-Matic, Follett, and other commercial ice machines — cleaning cycles, water filtration, refrigerant issues, control board replacements.' },
  { q: 'What refrigerants do you handle?', a: 'R-404A, R-134a, R-407A, R-448A, R-449A, R-513A, and lower-GWP replacements (R-454C, R-455A) being adopted under current EPA SNAP regulations. All techs are EPA 608 Universal certified.' },
  { q: 'Can you retrofit an older R-404A system?', a: 'In many cases yes — either a drop-in low-GWP replacement or a planned compressor change. R-404A service refrigerant has climbed sharply, so retrofit math often favors action before a major failure forces a rushed decision.' },
];

const related = [
  { href: '/services/ac-repair-tampa/', label: 'Commercial AC repair' },
  { href: '/services/hvac-installation-tampa/', label: 'Light-commercial HVAC' },
];

const areaLinks = [
  { href: '/service-areas/wesley-chapel-ac-repair/', label: 'Refrigeration repair in Wesley Chapel', note: 'Wiregrass · SR-54 retail corridor' },
  { href: '/service-areas/hillsborough-county-hvac-company/', label: 'Refrigeration repair in Tampa', note: 'Restaurants · convenience stores' },
  { href: '/service-areas/polk-county-residential-ac-repair/', label: 'Refrigeration repair in Polk County', note: 'Lakeland · Davenport hospitality' },
];
---
<ServiceLayout
  slug="refrigeration-repair-tampa"
  title="Commercial Refrigeration Repair in Wesley Chapel & Tampa FL | I Care Air Care"
  description="Wesley Chapel commercial refrigeration repair for restaurants, cafés, and small businesses across Tampa Bay. Walk-ins, reach-ins, ice machines. Call (813) 395-2324."
  h1="Commercial Refrigeration Repair in Wesley Chapel & Tampa Bay"
  eyebrow="Commercial Refrigeration · Wesley Chapel"
  subtitle={`When the walk-in goes down, revenue stops and product spoils. Our Wesley Chapel–based team services <span class="text-accent-400 font-semibold">commercial refrigeration across Tampa Bay</span> with fast emergency response and EPA-certified refrigerant work.`}
  heroImage="/images/HVAC-Services-in-Tampa-FL-%E2%80%93-Commercial-AC-Condenser-Systems.webp"
  serviceName="Commercial Refrigeration Repair"
  faqs={faqs}
  related={related}
  areaLinks={areaLinks}
  priceRange="$129-$880"
>
  <h2>Commercial refrigeration isn't just a bigger household fridge</h2>
  <p>Walk-in coolers, ice machines, and reach-ins run on different refrigerants, different control systems, and different duty cycles than residential equipment. A failed condenser fan on a restaurant walk-in isn't a $300 home repair — it's a $3,000 product loss if the wrong tech takes six hours diagnosing it. Our commercial techs are <strong>EPA 608 Universal certified</strong> and experienced on the equipment brands Tampa Bay businesses actually run.</p>

  <h2>Equipment we service</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Walk-in coolers & freezers</strong> — Kolpak, Bally, Master-Bilt, Nor-Lake, Arctic, Kysor-Warren</li>
    <li><strong>Reach-in refrigerators & freezers</strong> — True, Continental, Delfield, Beverage-Air, Traulsen, Turbo Air</li>
    <li><strong>Prep tables</strong> — Sandwich, pizza, salad, and refrigerated sushi prep cases</li>
    <li><strong>Ice machines</strong> — Manitowoc, Hoshizaki, Scotsman, Ice-O-Matic</li>
    <li><strong>Display cases</strong> — Open-front deli, bakery, and beverage merchandisers</li>
    <li><strong>Undercounters, back-bars, and beer coolers</strong></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Preventive maintenance keeps the doors open</h2>
  <p>Our commercial PM program includes quarterly or monthly visits depending on your equipment load:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Condenser coil cleaning (single biggest failure cause in Tampa humidity/kitchen grease environments)</li>
    <li>Evaporator coil inspection and defrost cycle verification</li>
    <li>Door gasket inspection and replacement (energy and food-safety critical)</li>
    <li>Condensate drain flushing and pan treatment</li>
    <li>Temperature calibration at rack controllers and individual cases</li>
    <li>Compressor amp draw and oil level check</li>
    <li>Refrigerant leak scan</li>
    <li>Written report for health-inspector records</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Emergency response that respects the clock</h2>
  <p>A walk-in failure can turn into a product-loss problem quickly. We prioritize operating businesses ahead of routine work when urgent refrigeration calls come in, then quote the repair path clearly before work begins.</p>

  <h2>2026 refrigerant regulations — what businesses need to know</h2>
  <p>The EPA's continued phase-down of high-GWP refrigerants is hitting commercial refrigeration hard in 2026. R-404A is largely phased out in new equipment and its service refrigerant cost has climbed significantly. If you're running equipment over 10 years old on R-404A, it's worth a conversation about <strong>retrofit options or scheduled replacement</strong> before a major failure forces a rushed decision. We'll give you honest numbers and timeline recommendations.</p>

  <p>Commercial refrigeration problem? <a href="tel:+18133952324">Call (813) 395-2324</a> and ask for the earliest available refrigeration appointment.</p>

  <h2>2026 commercial refrigeration pricing in Tampa Bay</h2>
  <div class="not-prose my-6 overflow-hidden rounded-xl ring-1 ring-slate-200">
    <table class="w-full text-sm">
      <thead class="bg-surface text-navy-700">
        <tr><th class="text-left py-2 px-4 font-semibold">Service</th><th class="text-left py-2 px-4 font-semibold">2026 flat-rate</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="text-slate-700">
        {refrigPrices.map(p => (
          <tr class="border-t border-slate-100"><td class="py-2 px-4">{p.item}</td><td class="py-2 px-4 font-mono">${p.min.toLocaleString()}{p.max !== p.min ? `–$${p.max.toLocaleString()}` : ''}</td></tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <Schema
    slot="extraSchema"
    type="PriceSpecificationList"
    prices={refrigPrices}
    pageId={`${SITE.url}/services/refrigeration-repair-tampa/`}
    data={{ name: '2026 commercial refrigeration repair pricing in Tampa Bay' }}
  />
</ServiceLayout>
